text: Kumari Meche is a Nepali communist politician and a member of the House of Representatives of the federal parliament of Nepal. She was elected from CPN UML under the proportional representation system filling the reserved seat for women and indigenous groups. She represents Nepal Communist Party (NCP), the new party formed by the merger of CPN UML with CPN (Maoist Centre), in the parliament.
